      <p>Learn about the balance and clarity of Classical music through the works of Haydn, Mozart, and Beethoven. Understand sonata form and classical style traits.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="lesson" id="lesson5">
      <h2>Lesson 5: Romantic Era</h2>
      <p>Explore emotional expression and individualism in music through composers like Chopin, Schumann, and Tchaikovsky. Learn about program music and nationalism.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="lesson" id="lesson6">
      <h2>Lesson 6: 20th Century Music</h2>
      <p>Dive into modernism, impressionism, and experimental music. Discover how Stravinsky, Debussy, and Cage changed the soundscape of the 1900s.</p>
    </div>
